02 7:46:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=186>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixing wizards: my recommendations (long)</span><hr size=1> Not very well thought out in my opinion.  If you want to reach x figure of dmg over time why not increase manna regen instead?  Increasing the full burn dmg by a large amount would imply rebalancing high lvl encounters especially those with banable mobs.<br>
<br>
One problem you may see with that type of suggestion is the desire not to devalue the flowing joke items that are allready dropping off very high end mobs even if adding substantally better manna regen items in substantially easier encounters would be a good thing for class balance.<br>
<br>
If you do feel the need for clickable dmg items it would be of substantial benifit to you as a class and to the eq game world as a whole that these items not be usable below the lvl range they are intended to be used it.  <br>
<br>
Making them twinkable would simply lead to wizard twinks and greater inbalance vs non twinks especially in pvp. <br>
<br>
Currently the rogue class is besieged and diluted by a legion of twinks. Why? Because its easy to put a high lvl weapon in a low lvl rogues hand and do unbalanced dmg and lvl easily. Do you really want to see something similar happen to wizards if they were made a viable and desirable class in exp groups due to the changes you desire comming into being? Do you really want to hear discussions that go like &quot;My lvl 20 wizard roxors! he can nuke for 200 dmg with his rod of pwnage! No way man he suxors mine can do 300 with his kaboom uber stick!&quot;  Wait on second though maybe the kool doodz will stop playing their rogue twinks /cheer!<br>
<br>
Regarding &quot;up time&quot; a near 100% uptime group is quite possible. Example...<br>
<br>
Best exp group in my opinion is monk warrior rogue rogue enchanter cleric.<br>
<br>
How do you get near 100% uptime with this group? Simple.<br>
<br>
First you have a monk chain pull groups or single mobs as you prefer to the waiting group.  Chain pulling implies that the puller will leave to pull more mobs before the group finishes the current pull and will have the new mobs there shortly after the first pull takes a dirt nap.<br>
<br>
Your warrior gets on a target and taunts it.<br>
<br>
Rogues and monk assist the warrior.<br>
<br>
Enchanter mezes the rest then slows the target.<br>
<br>
Cleric Cheals as neccesary when the warrior drops down to 40% hp healing the warrior several thousand hp each time.<br>
<br>
Cleric clicks pog or velious quest legs if neccesary and if they have em when not chealing or medding. This is about a 100 group heal.<br>
<br>
Rogues and warrior click pog or velious quest bp between kills this is around a 90 hp heal every 15 seconds.<br>
<br>
Monk regens via fungi tunic, iksar regen (if applicable), mend, occasional celestial heals, coldain ring (if they have it) while pulling said monk should have run speed 3 allowing them to take very little dmg on the pull as they can outrun the mobs easily.<br>
<br>
Realize that almost all of the dmg taken here will be by a high lvl warrior tanking 1 70% slowed mob at a time and getting healed in an EXTREMELY effecient manner.  Then look at the fact that 60s can gain alt exp by killing high 40s mobs that are still dark blue and see how much downtime you have.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<br>Need a log parsed?</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/15/02 10:31:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=187>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixing wizards: my recommendations (long)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Not very well thought out in my opinion.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I welcome feedback from all sources, even Rogues who play on PvP servers.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If you want to reach x figure of dmg over time why not increase manna regen instead?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Increasing mana regen is also a reasonable solution. However, increased mana regen affects all spells (including snares and AE spells), while targeting the efficiency boost at DD spells allows for a more precise balanacing effort without unwanted side effects such as improving the ability of wizards to quad kite.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Increasing the full burn dmg by a large amount would imply rebalancing high lvl encounters especially those with banable mobs.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Reducing mana cost for spells and adding right click nukes do not increase full burn damage rate at all. It would increase the effective mana pool of wizards when attacking a single target, but I'm not aware of this being a balance issue at the moment. If Banes become unbalanced, then it would be reasonable to leave the mana cost alone or give a smaller cut in cost than for other spells. For GB, however, agro is usually the limiting factor, and it's already close for DB on some of the longer fights, so I suspect that reducing the mana cost on these spells would have very little effect on the end game.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If you do feel the need for clickable dmg items it would be of substantial benifit to you as a class and to the eq game world as a whole that these items not be usable below the lvl range they are intended to be used it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Erm... right click items already work this way... They do not activate if the user is not of sufficient level. This is one of the main differences between melee twink items and caster twink items.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Making them twinkable would simply lead to wizard twinks and greater inbalance vs non twinks especially in pvp.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
The problem with twinks is very pervasive in EQ, and is not an easy one to solve. What we are striving for here is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> balance,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and for lower level wizards on mature servers, balance is sorely lacking, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> especially</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in the PvP realm.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Regarding &quot;up time&quot; a near 100% uptime group is quite possible. Example...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
While this is a decent plan, practical experience has shown that it does not attain 100% uptime. The highest single group uptime I've seen was around 70%, and it is more common for fast pull groups to achieve closer to 50% uptime. This came as quite a surprise to me as well, but the logs provided me with some surprising evidence (including how much action there was in a &quot;slow pull group&quot;). I would love to be proven wrong, and be supplied with a log from a single group of 6 where kill rate was anywhere close to 100%, but I haven't seen one yet.<br>
<br>
... but your illustration of the perfect single pull group helps to underscore our point:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Best exp group in my opinion is monk warrior rogue rogue enchanter cleric.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Why no wizard? The answer is well known, and is why wizards are in need of balancing: the Wizard will not be able to keep up with the pulls. Reducing mana cost of DDs and adding more right click nukes will help to address this issue and will at least make them viable. We are not asking to supplant rogues as the kings of sustainable damage (don't worry, your position is secure). We are just seeking some balance between melee classes and mana classes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uthediscoinferno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The DiscoInferno</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/15/02 11:57:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=188>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixing wizards: my recommendations (long)</span><hr size=1> instead of upping regen (which verant seems to loath the thought of) Why not just put in the damned focus items? Treat focus items like weapons for melee and the mudflation problem is countered <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/15/02 1:16:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=189>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixing wizards: my recommendations (long)</span><hr size=1> But what ARE focus items?  All we have is speculation.  I don't want to go to VI and say &quot;please put in focus items&quot;, then be surprised 2 weeks later when I find &quot;+5% Evoc damage, +10% aggro&quot; focus items. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
<br>Wizard of the 40th Season
<br>Guild Leader of Nightwatch of Norrath
<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn
<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27902" target="_blank">Look down my pants with Magelo!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>(Title left blank)</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/15/02 3:17:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=190>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> foci</span><hr size=1> Yeah I wouldn't hang too much of your hopes on these things, why would Verant utterly reverse 3 years of work and make bitchen items for casters?  Making caster SPELLS work better is the correct step, but that won't happen either. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/15/02 7:25:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=191>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: foci</span><hr size=1> Good point on the agro issue on full burn dmg.  Btw as far as pvp on mature servers.  Low lvl wizards do quite well when not fighting twinks.  The practical solution for pvp twinking is to give weapons a lvl limit on a pvp server.  Every twink lvl 6 warrior with a lamentation would scream in anger but in in the end it would be a good change for pvp servers.<br>
<br>
I will log my next experience group, even if it isn't the best possible group I'm betting on more than 70% uptime.<br>
<br>
I believe whatever change is neccesary should be in the form of gear (as suggested by others before) rather than being handed out for free in keeping with the spirit of the game and balance between players.  Items that reduce the cost of evocation spells by a fixed percentage wouldn't be too bad.  Btw what sort of group should wizards be balanced in, the 30% uptime one or the 70% one?<br>
<br>
One more note on logging and comparing dmg.  If in the course of trying to achieve your best possible dmg you draw agro frequently you will not be taking an accurate log.  One problem I have with casters in general is agro especially when people have the badly mistaken idea that their expience bar matters in a raid setting.  This is what happens in a raid setting when a caster overnukes...<br>
<br>
All the rogues loss the chance to backstab until everyone repositions, this cuts their dmg by around 30%.<br>
<br>
All melees lose several rounds of melee while people find the  mob and engage again.<br>
<br>
The MA loses taunt and more importantly can no longer hit the mob till he finds it and engages it again resulting in even less agro on him and even more chance of the next nuke by anyone sending the mob running around after the caster.<br>
<br>
Basicly overagroing as a caster can be like casting an AE slow on your entire raid.  It's my impression that bad ping pong in a large group of people fighting player sized mobs cuts my dmg by at least 50-60%. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<br>Err, Forum Arch Mage?</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/16/02 2:54:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=192>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixing wizards: my recommendations (long)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> One more note on logging and comparing dmg. If in the course of trying to achieve your best possible dmg you draw agro frequently you will not be taking an accurate log. One problem I have with casters in general is agro especially when people have the badly mistaken idea that their expience bar matters in a raid setting. This is what happens in a raid setting when a caster overnukes...<br>
<br>
All the rogues loss the chance to backstab until everyone repositions, this cuts their dmg by around 30%.<br>
<br>
All melees lose several rounds of melee while people find the mob and engage again.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->You are making a couple bad assumptions here.<br>
<br>
1.  That a wizard pushing his dps will draw aggro frequently.<br>
<br>
2.  A mob aggroed on a wizard automatically ping pongs.<br>
<br>
Good wizards on a raid will not draw aggro &quot;frequently&quot; and when he does, he'll either draw aggro just as the mob dies(often taking zero damage) or he'll be in melee range so the mob does not ping pong.<br>
<br>
Ping pong can be good sometimes too..<br>
<br>
The other people that are all trying to get xp are the melees, and will often conveniently ignore commands to reposition a mob getting dangerously far from the camp.  That's the time when you drag the mob to a good spot using aggro.<br>
<br>
Of course this doesn't work well on dragons and bosses and such... but honestly I've never had a problem with people trying to get xp on those mobs.  It's only the trash mobs that don't matter anyway that has everyone gunning for xp.  <br>
